'''ယျင်ဟဳ လဳ (Yanghee Lee)''' (ကိုဝ်ရဳယာ: 이양희; ဟာန်ဇ: 李亮喜, သၠးဂဝ် ၂၄ ဂျူလာင် ၁၉၅၆) ဝွံ ဒှ်တၠပညာစိတ္တဗေဒ မဆေင်ကဵု ပရေင်ဇၞော်မောဝ် ကောန်ဍုင် ကိုဝ်ရဳယျာ သၠုင်ကျာ၊ ပါမောက္ခ တက္ကသိုလ် သံင်ကျုန်ကွာန် (Sungkyunkwan University) ရ။ ညးဝွံ နကဵု ဗွိုင်ဂၠးတိမ္ဂး ဒှ်မၞိဟ် မဂွံတီကေတ် ညးမကၠောန်ကမၠောန် ပ္ဍဲဂကောံအခေါင်အရာမၞိဟ် ဂၠးတိ။ နကဵု ကုလသမဂ္ဂ ခပတိုန်လဝ်ညး နဒဒှ် မၞိဟ်လ္ၚတ် ကိစ္စအခေါင်အရာမၞိဟ် ပ္ဍဲကၟိန်ဍုင်ဗၟာမွဲတၠရ။ 

== ပရေင်ပညာ ==
လဳ ကလိဂွံ တဆိပ်ဒဳဂရဳ (B.S.) နူကဵု တက္ကသိုလ် Georgetown University မဒှ်တက္ကသိုလ် နူကဵု ကၟိန်ဍုင်အမေရိကာန်ရ။ တုဲညးဆက်တိုန် တက္ကသိုလ်မိသ်သောရဳ (University of Missouri) တုဲ ကလိဂွံ တဆိပ်ကြာ M.ED. ကေုာံ ပဳအုက်ဒဳ(ဒံက်တာ) ရ။<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ohchr.org/EN/HRBodies/SP/CountriesMandates/MM/Pages/SRMyanmar.aspx|title=Special Rapporteur on the situation of human rights in Myanmar|work=[[Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights]]|date=|accessdate=17 May 2018|language=en}}</ref>

== ကမၠောန် အခေါင်အရာမၞိဟ် ကေုာံ တာလျိုင် ပ္ဍဲ ကုလသမဂ္ဂ ==
Yanghee Lee currently serves on the Advisory committee of the National Human Rights Commission of Korea. She is the founding President of the [http://incrc.org/eng/?ckattempt=1 International Child Rights Center], a non-profit organization based in Seoul. In 2009, she received the Order of Civil Merit, the highest recognition given to a civilian in Korea, for her work in human rights.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/news/government-removes-welcome-mat-un-special-rapporteur.html|work=[[The Myanmar Times]]|title=Government removes welcome mat for UN Special Rapporteur|date=21 December 2017|accessdate=17 May 2018|language=en}}</ref>

Lee served as chairperson of the Committee on the Rights of the Child under the UN High Commissioner for Human Rights from 2007 to 2011. She also served as chairperson of the [https://www.ohchr.org/EN/HRBodies/AnnualMeeting/Pages/Meetingchairpersons.aspx Meeting of Chairpersons of Human Rights Treaty Bodies] from 2010 to 2011.

Lee was appointed special rapporteur of the UN on the situation of human rights in Myanmar first established in 1992 under the Commission on Human Rights Resolution 58 and extended annually. Following usual practice, her appointment as special rapporteur on the situation of human rights in Myanmar was extended for one year in March 2019.  The Myanmar government, however, has denied access to Yanghee Lee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=22553|title=OHCHR - Myanmar refuses access to UN Special Rapporteur}} See also {{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/12/myanmar-bars-human-rights-envoy-yanghee-lee-171220145600876.html|title=Myanmar bars UN human rights envoy Yanghee Lee}} and {{Cite web|url=https://frontiermyanmar.net/en/rakhine-conflict-has-hallmarks-of-genocide-yanghee-lee|title=Rakhine conflict has 'hallmarks of genocide': Yanghee Lee}}</ref>

Lee is highly recognized nationally, regionally, and internationally for her expertise in human rights. She has published numerous articles and books on human rights and children’s rights. She was awarded the 2009 Human Rights Award of Korea, as winner.

